{"annotations": [{"id": ["NCBIGene:2099"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ERa", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9802863001823425, "span": {"begin": 0, "end": 3}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:16469"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "17&beta;-estradiol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9996158480644226, "span": {"begin": 40, "end": 58}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2099"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ER&alpha", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9201698303222656, "span": {"begin": 204, "end": 212}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "estrogen responsive elements", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.9216160178184509, "span": {"begin": 233, "end": 261}}, {"id": ["mesh:D004967"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "estrogen", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9900004267692566, "span": {"begin": 233, "end": 241}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "EREs", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.8562655448913574, "span": {"begin": 263, "end": 267}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2033"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "p300", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9967398047447205, "span": {"begin": 485, "end": 489}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1977"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CBP", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9919050931930542, "span": {"begin": 490, "end": 493}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:10498"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CARM1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9902296662330627, "span": {"begin": 498, "end": 503}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "chromatin", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.8709766864776611, "span": {"begin": 515, "end": 524}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "target", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.5204226970672607, "span": {"begin": 634, "end": 640}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "EREs", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.656873345375061, "span": {"begin": 754, "end": 758}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "promoter", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.6544314026832581, "span": {"begin": 766, "end": 774}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6925"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "ERE E2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9937556982040405, "span": {"begin": 856, "end": 862}}], "text": "ERa is one of the receptor-recruited by 17&beta;-estradiol (E2) able to influences a wide range of biological phenomena, from fertility to memory formation (Dahlman-Wright et al., 2006). Ligand-activated ER&alpha; interacts with the estrogen responsive elements (EREs) on the DNA, in turn inducing or repressing gene transcription. Transcriptional regulation is ruled by the interaction with coregulators that can enhance or decrease the transcriptional activity. Coregulators such as p300/CBP and CARM1 may affect chromatin modification and remodelling through epigenetic activity (Liang &amp; Shang, 2013). In addition, for several target genes the specific mechanisms by which E2 regulates their expression remains unknown because they lack canonical EREs in the promoter. It has thus been hypothesized that besides the classical genomic action through ERE E2 may regulate gene expression downstream to the activation of epigenetic mechanisms.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:07:41 +0000 2026"}